<title>Interactive Fighting/Dancing Scenarios</title>
<h1>Interactive Fighting/Dancing Scenarios</h1>
<b>
All scenarios should be recorded as a video clip
of no longer than 55 seconds.  The deliverables
include the recorded video clip (both as a video file and on YouTube), the source code, the user/actor manual
or readme file, with the implementation procedure
included as an appendix of the user/actor manual.
<p>
<h2>Scenario 1: <font color=red>Boring Boxing by a Bored Boxer</font> (Act 2)</h2>
The actor would draw the character meaning "bored",
then point at a "gate" and draw a "heart" to create
the same character, and then draw a "gate" and
point at the "heart" to create the same, etc.
<p>
<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RaqEoOftr7I">A demo to draw a Chinese character meaning "bored" using gestures</a>
<p>
<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wHvA22VHxJo">Same demo but in faster speed</a>

<p>
<h2>Scenario 2: <font color=red>4D MailBox</font> (Act 2)</h2>
The actor would open a mailbox in mid air and point
at objects inside to open the letter.

<p>
<h2>Scenario 3: <font color=red>Dance of the TotalHistorians Version I</font> (Act 3 Scene 1)</h2>
The Kinect program to track multiple full-body motions
can be used to create/mimic the dancers (the TotalHistorians) on the screen,
albeit with more gimmicks.
<p>
<h2>Scenario 4: <font color=red>Dance of the TotalHistorians Version II</font> (Act 3 Scene 1)</h2>
The symbol of the TotalHistory is a circle, or
Wheel of Fortune.  The TotalHistorians will interact
with a circle on the screen to create various
visual effects.
<p>
<h2>Scenario 5: <font color=red>First fight between our hero and the Snakeman</font> (Act 4 Scene 3)</h2>
The hero uses the Wheel of Fortune to escape, with
the Snakeman chasing from historical period to
historical period.
<p>
<h2>Scenario 6: <font color=red>Second fight between our hero and the Snakeman</font> (Act 7)</h2>
The hero tries to activate a safety valve (?) on
the wall (screen), while the Snakeman is doing its
best to prevent that from happening, with visual
effects.

<p>
<h2>Scenario 7: <font color=red>Vicious Snakeman Version I</font> (TBD)</h2>
The Snakeman uses a gesture to throw a physical object
(perhaps a block or a robot car) into the virtual world.
<p>
<h2>Scenario 8: <font color=red>Vicious Snakeman Version II</font> (TBD)</h2>
To be determined

<p>
<h2>Scenario 9: <font color=red>Fate Teller</font> (Intermission)</h2>
The audience can go to the kiosk during intermission
and use fist/finger to determine whether the story
has a happy ending or sad ending.
